at triggers JDK AWT/Swing native initialization and fails inside `java.awt.Component.initIDs()` with `java.lang.NoSuchFieldError: java.awt.Component.isPacked`. The second failure is then just a follow-on `NoClassDefFoundError` because `PropertyBoundTextField` could not finish class initialization.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldSyncsInitialAndUpdatedBeanValue()`\\n\\n- Failure: `java.lang.NoSuchFieldError: java.awt.Component.isPacked`\\n- Root cause: non-metadata-related native-image desktop/JNI initialization issue in JDK AWT/Swing.\\n- Why this is not library metadata: the failure occurs in `java.desktop` while initializing `java.awt.Component`, before any missing `com.mchange` reachability entry is reported. This is a JDK desktop support problem, not missing library metadata for `mchange-commons-java`.\\n\\n### `propertyBoundTextFieldAppliesUserChangesBackToBean()`\\n\\n- Failure: `java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Could not initialize class com.mchange.v2.beans.swing.PropertyBoundTextField`\\n- Root cause: same underlying AWT/Swing initialization failure as above.\\n- Why this is not library metadata: this is only the cascading error after the first test already failed class initialization.\\n\\n## Intervention\\n\\nRemoved the generated test file:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.mchange/mchange-commons-java/0.2.15/src/test/java/com_mchange/mchange_commons_java/PropertyComponentBindingUtilityTest.java`\\n\\nNo metadata files were modified.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated coverage is still valuable and passed after removing the Swing-only test. It continues to validate native-image behavior for the library's reflection, proxies, serialization, naming, logging, thread-pool, collection, JDBC, XML, and codegen utilities.\\n\\nRemoving the single Swing/AWT-native test avoids chasing JDK desktop internals in library metadata while preserving the broader generated support that does e