.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/WindowUtilsMacWindowUtils1Test.java`\\n\\nAfter removing those generated tests, `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=net.java.dev.jna:jna-platform:5.8.0 --stacktrace` passed.\\n\\n## Root cause by failing test\\n\\n### 1. `ConvertTest.toVariantUsesMatchingVariantConstructorForCompatibleReferenceTypes()`\\n\\n**Classification:** not metadata-related\\n\\n**Why it failed:** native image failed while JNA initialized `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Variant$VARIANT` and its nested Win32 structure/union types. The failure chain ends in constructor-instantiation problems such as:\\n- `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.OaIdl$CURRENCY$_CURRENCY.<init>()`\\n- `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.WinDef$BYTE.<init>()`\\n\\nThese are JNA/native-image structure-instantiation limitations for nested Win32 wrapper types, not missing reachability metadata. The error is an `IllegalArgumentException`/`NoSuchMethodException` during JNA structure validation, not a `Missing*RegistrationError`.\\n\\n**Action:** removed `ConvertTest.java`.\\n\\n### 2. `ConvertTest.toJavaObjectRestoresComEnumsViaTheirValuesMethod()`\\n\\n**Classification:** not metadata-related\\n\\n**Why it failed:** this test failed only because `Variant.VARIANT` had already failed to initialize for the same reason as the previous test. The reported `NoClassDefFoundError` is a consequence of the earlier JNA `VARIANT` initialization failure, not missing metadata.\\n\\n**Action:** removed `ConvertTest.java`.\\n\\n### 3. `WindowUtilsMacWindowUtils1Test.macWindowAlphaRunnableUsesWindowPeerAlphaSetter()`\\n\\n**Classification:** not metadata-related\\n\\n**Why it failed:** the test forces initialization of AWT `Window`/`Component` machinery while exercising `WindowUtils$MacWindowUtils` in a Linux native-image run. The failure comes from unsupported AWT/JNI platform internals (`java.awt.event.KeyEvent.isProxyActive` / `KeyEvent` initialization mismatch), which is a platform/runtime limitation rather than missing metadata.\\n\\nThis is also a macOS-specific behavior test being executed in a Linux native-image environment.\\n\\n**Action:** removed `WindowUtilsMacWindowUtils1Test.java`.\\n\\n## Metadata-related failures preserved\\n\\nThe Codex log also showed two earlier native-image failures in:\\n- `OaIdlUtilTest.toPrimitiveArrayCreatesNestedJavaArraysFromSafeArrayDimensions()`\\n- `OaIdlUtilTest.toPrimitiveArrayDestroysTheSafeArrayWhenRequested()`\\n\\nThose were metadata-related because they raised a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for:\\n\\n- `com.sun.jna.platform.win32.OaIdl$SAFEARRAYBOUND`\\n- constructor `public com.sun.jna.platform.win32.OaIdl$SAFEARRAYBOUND(com.sun.jna.Pointer)`\\n\\nCodex identified and added that missing metadata, so those tests were preserved and now pass. No further metadata changes were made in this intervention.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still provides useful coverage for `jna-platform:5.8.0`:\\n- Win32 exception handling\\n- DDE helper behavior\\n- file monitoring\\n- enum conversion helpers\\n- `OaIdlUtil` SAFEARRAY handling\\n- TLB template/resource loading\\n- X11 window utility behavior\\n\\nThose areas now pass in native image and validate real library behavior that is still relevant for this coordinate. The removed tests were narrow cases blocked by native-image/JNA/AWT platform limitations, not evidence that the rest of the generated support is invalid.\"\n    },\n    \"metrics\": {\n      \"input_tokens_used\": 1650816,\n      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 20681344,\n      \"output_tokens_used\": 219163,\n      \"iterations\": 29,\n      \"cost_usd\": 8.4577,\n      \"generated_loc\": 889,\n      \"tested_library_loc\": 446,\n      \"metadata_entries\": 110,\n      \"code_coverage_percent\": 3.21\n    },\n    \"artifacts\": {\n      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.8.0/src/test/java/net_java_dev_