\n        \"line\": {\n          \"covered\": 909,\n          \"missed\": 2559,\n          \"ratio\": 0.262111,\n          \"total\": 3468\n        },\n        \"method\": {\n          \"covered\": 174,\n          \"missed\": 612,\n          \"ratio\": 0.221374,\n          \"total\": 786\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"post_generation_intervention\": {\n      \"stage\": \"metadata_fix_failed\",\n      \"intervention_file\": \"post-gen-interventions/org.jboss.logmanager_jboss-logmanager_1.2.0.GA.md\",\n      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe native image built successfully, and the remaining failures were two native-runtime behavioral assertions rather than missing reachability metadata. There was no `Missing*RegistrationError` in the Gradle failure output. The generated support should therefore be kept, but the two unsupported native-only tests were removed.\\n\\nI also confirmed that the generated test suite passes on the JVM and that `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA --stacktrace` passes after removing the two failing native-only tests.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. `org.jboss.logmanager.LogManagerTest > readConfigurationFallsBackToLogManagerClassLoaderWhenContextClassLoaderRejectsConfigurator()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** `LogManager.construct(...)` uses `Class.forName(name, true, contextClassLoader)` first and then falls back to the `LogManager` class loader. In the native image, the assertion `rejectingClassLoader.rejectedClassLoadAttempted` stayed `false`, even though the configurator was still instantiated successfully.\\n- **Interpretation:** this test depends on observing a custom `ClassLoader.loadClass(...)` rejection path for an image-contained class. That is a native-image class-loading behavior difference, not missing metadata. If metadata were missing, the failure would have been a registration error or reflective instantiation failure, not a plain `assertThat(...).isTrue()` failure.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and its test-only helpers from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/LogManagerTest.java`.\\n\\n### 2. `org.jboss.logmanager.formatters.Formatters12Test > extendedExceptionFormattingUsesClassLoadingFallbacksAndClassResourceLookup()`\\n\\n- **Root cause:** not metadata-related.\\n- **Why:** the native failure was again a boolean assertion (`loadedFromBytes`, `rejectedSystemTargetAttempted`, or `classResourceRequested`) staying `false`, not a missing registration error. This test tries to verify that `%E` formatting forces a custom context class loader to byte-define a target class and then performs `.class` resource lookup through that loader.\\n- **Interpretation:** the formatter output path is preserved, but the test relies on runtime-observable custom class loading and resource lookup behavior that native image does not preserve in the same way for image-contained classes. The native image already built successfully, so this is not evidence of missing metadata.\\n- **Action taken:** removed that test method and the test-only helper loader/classes that existed solely for it from `tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/formatters/Formatters12Test.java`.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still exercises meaningful `jboss-logmanager` behavior that is relevant to reachability metadata:\\n\\n- context-class-loader-based configurator and locator instantiation still has coverage\\n- bootstrap fallback for exception formatting still has coverage\\n- privileged exception class resource lookup still has coverage\\n- property-based handler/filter/formatter/error-manager configuration still has coverage\\n- serialization-related coverage for the map implementations still has coverage\\n- default configuration lookup and typed array handling still have coverage\\n\\nIn short, only the two tests that depended on native-image-incompatible custom class-loading observability were removed. The rest of the generated suite still validates real library behavior and should be preserved.\"\n    },\n    \"metrics\": {\n      \"input_tokens_used\": 316687,\n      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 3697536,\n      \"output_tokens_used\": 68274,\n      \"iterations\": 10,\n      \"cost_usd\": 1.9485,\n      \"generated_loc\": 718,\n      \"tested_library_loc\": 4561,\n      \"metadata_entries\": 25,\n      \"code_coverage_percent\": 26.16\n    },\n    \"artifacts\": {\n      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org/jboss/logmanager/AtomicArrayTest.java\",\n      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/reachability-metadata.json\"\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-20T21:51:32.219175Z\",\n    \"library\": \"org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\",\n    \"starting_commit\": \"32b6870b543dba3cc7fb066d84d4ef79a9dc234b\",\n    \"ending_commit\": \"384c39a55040405c319e88c0081c77f8848d7526\",\n    \"strategy_name\": \"dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4\",\n    \"agent\": \"pi\",\n    \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.4\",\n    \"status\": \"success_with_intervention\",\n    \"stats\": {\n      \"version\": \"1.2.0.GA\",\n      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n        \"breakdown\": {\n          \"reflection\": {\n            \"coverageRatio\": 0.9375,\n            \"coveredCalls\": 30,\n            \"totalCalls\": 32\n          },\n          \"resources\": {\n            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n            \"coveredCalls\": 3,\n            \"totalCalls\": 3\n          }\n        },\n        \"coverageRatio\": 0.942857,\n        \"coveredCalls\": 33,\n        \"totalCalls\": 35\n      },\n      \"libraryCoverage\": {\n        \"instruction\": {\n          \"covered\": 3653,\n          \"missed\": 10531,\n          \"ratio\": 0.257544,\n          \"total\": 14184\n        },\n        \"line\": {\n          \"covered\": 903,\n          \"missed\": 2565,\n          \"ratio\": 0.260381,\n          \"total\": 3468\n        },\n        \"method\": {\n          \"covered\": 185,\n          \"missed\": 601,\n          \"ratio\": 0.235369,\n          \"total\": 786\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"post_generation_intervention\": {\n      \"stage\": \"metadata_fix_failed\",\n      \"intervention_file\": \"post-gen-interventions/org.jboss.logmanager_jboss-logmanager_1.2.0.GA.md\",\n      \"analysis_markdown\": \"# Post-generation intervention report\\n\\nLibrary: org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA\\nStage: `metadata_fix_failed`\\n\\n## Summary\\n\\nThe post-generation failures had two different causes:\\n\\n1. `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()` in the Codex metadata-fix log was **metadata-related**.\\n2. `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` in the final Gradle failure was **not metadata-related**; it depended on JVM class-loader fallback behavior that does not hold under Native Image.\\n\\nI removed the generated `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()` test and kept the rest of the generated support.\\n\\n## Failure analysis\\n\\n### 1. Codex log failure: metadata-related\\n\\nThe Codex log shows a `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` from:\\n\\n- `ConcurrentReferenceHashMapTest.serializationRoundTripPreservesEntries()`\\n\\nMissing entry reported by Native Image:\\n\\n- `java.util.concurrent.locks.ReentrantLock$Sync.readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream)`\\n\\nThat failure came from Java deserialization of `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap`, so it was a real reachability-metadata gap rather than a bad test. This support should be preserved because it covers an actual native-image requirement for the library's serialization path.\\n\\n### 2. Remaining Gradle failure: not metadata-related\\n\\nThe remaining failing test was:\\n\\n- `Formatters12Test.extendedExceptionFormattingFallsBackToCallerLoaderWhenTcclRejectsTheStackFrameClass()`\\n\\nThis failed on:\\n\\n- `assertThat(rejectingClassLoader.wasRejected()).isTrue()`\\n\\nRoot cause:\\n\\n- The test assumes the formatter will first try to resolve the stack-frame class through the thread context class loader, observe a `ClassNotFoundException`, and only then fall back to the caller loader.\\n- In Native Image, class resolution for already-linked image classes does not preserve that JVM class-loading interaction in the same way. The formatted stack trace is still produced, but the custom rejecting loader is never asked to load the class, so `wasRejected()` stays `false`.\\n- No `Missing*RegistrationError` was reported for this failure, so this was not a metadata problem.\\n\\nThis is therefore a Native Image class-loading/runtime-semantics issue in the generated test, and removing that generated test was the correct intervention.\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe rest of the generated support still exercises real library behavior and should remain in place:\\n\\n- serialization coverage for `ConcurrentReferenceHashMap` and `FastCopyHashMap`\\n- resource lookup coverage for `DefaultConfigurationLocator`\\n- formatter/resource coverage in `Formatters12Test`\\n- configuration loading and component instantiation coverage in `LogManagerTest` and `PropertyConfiguratorTest`\\n\\nAfter removing only the non-metadata-related formatter fallback test, the coordinate passed again with:\\n\\n- `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n- `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.logmanager:jboss-logmanager:1.2.0.GA`\\n\\nSo the generated metadata-backed support is still valuable and should be kept; only the unsupported caller-loader fallback assertion needed to be dropped.\"\n    },\n    \"metrics\": {\n      \"input_tokens_used\": 453851,\n      \"cached_input_tokens_used\": 5017472,\n      \"output_tokens_used\": 76101,\n      \"iterations\": 16,\n      \"cost_usd\": 2.3959,\n      \"generated_loc\": 704,\n      \"tested_library_loc\": 903,\n      \"metadata_entries\": 16,\n      \"code_coverage_percent\": 26.04\n    },\n    \"artifacts\": {\n      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/src/test/java/org_jboss_logmanager/jboss_logmanager/LogManagerTest.java\",\n      \"metadata_file\": \"metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/reachability-metadata.json\"\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    \"timestamp\": \"2026-04-17T20:16:35.872241Z\",\n    \"library\": \"org.jboss.narayana.jta:jta:5.12.4.Final\",\n    \"starting_commit\": \"dc5bb2d3277f2cf3005c468383476ec86f7d01c2\",\n    \"ending_commit\": \"f77416bd5af3da24a8ed8144e5574850d01dab02\",\n    \"strategy_name\": \"dynamic_access_main_sources_pi_gpt-5.4\",\n    \"agent\": \"pi\",\n    \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.4\",\n    \"status\": \"success_with_intervention\",\n    \"stats\": {\n      \"version\": \"5.12.4.Final\",\n      \"dynamicAccess\": {\n        \"breakdown\": {\n          \"reflection\": {\n            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n            \"coveredCalls\": 8,\n            \"totalCalls\": 8\n          }\n        },\n        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n        \"coveredCalls\": 8,\n        \"totalCalls\": 8\n      },\n      \"libraryCoverage\": {\n        \"instruction\": {\n          \"covered\": 759,\n          \"missed\": 18148,\n          \"ratio\": 0.040144,\n          \"total\": 18907\n        },\n        \"line\": {\n          \"covered\": 222,\n          \"missed\": 4903,\n          \"ratio\": 0.043317,\n          \"total\": 5125\n        },\n        \"method\": {\