rialized a `java.lang.String` field inside that object graph.\\n- Root cause: **incomplete test-only serialization metadata**, not an unsupported native-image behavior.\\n- This test should be preserved because it validates real serialization behavior inside `XAOnePhaseResource.pack/unpack`.\\n\\n### `XAResourceRecordTest.saveAndRestoreStateWithSerializableXaResource()`\\n\\n- This failed for the same reason as `XAOnePhaseResourceTest`: the serialized object graph used by `XAResourceRecord.save_state/restore_state` needed complete serialization registration.\\n- The Codex log shows the failure narrowing to missing serialization constructor support, which is metadata-related.\\n- The earlier excerpt also showed reflective/environment initialization issues while entering Narayana state-management code; those are consistent with the same metadata-fix workflow being incomplete rather than a test defect.\\n- This test should be preserved because it covers real native-image-sensitive behavior in `XAResourceRecord` state save/restore.\\n\\n## Why the generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support is valid and should stay because it enables genuine native-image coverage instead of masking a bad test:\\n\\n- `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/org.jboss.narayana.jta.jta.tests/serialization-config.json` is required for the two serialization-based tests.\\n- Those tests exercise real Narayana code paths that serialize and deserialize XA-related state.\\n- Deleting the tests would reduce coverage of legitimate native-image requirements for this library.\\n\\n## Outcome\\n\\nNo generated tests were removed.\\n\\nAfter preserving the generated test-only serialization support, the focused native lane succeeds:\\n\\n- `./gradlew nativeTest -Pcoordinates=org.jboss.narayana.jta:jta:5.12.4.Final --stacktrace`\\n\\nSo the correct intervention here is to **keep** the generated tests and preserve the generated test-only support rather than delete coverag